@@TJvErrorControl
Summary
  A control that can display and optionally blink an image.
Description
  TJvErrorControl is the class used for the error icons created by an error indicator. Do not create
  instances of TJvErrorControl yourself. TJvErrorControl instances are created and maintained by
  TJvErrorIndicator as needed.
See Also
  TJvErrorIndicator

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvErrorControl.BlinkCount
Summary
  Specifies the number of times the icon should blink.
Description
  Read BlinkCount to determine how many times the image is blinked by the control. Change BlinkCount to
  set the number of times the icon should be blinked. While a blink is in progress, this value is
  automatically decremented.

  The BlinkCount property is handled by the owning TJvErrorIndicator and should not normally be altered
  unless you are writing your own error indicator.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvErrorControl.CalcBoundsRect
Summary
  Calculates the size and location of the control.
Description
  CalcBoundsRect calculates the suggested size and location of the control. The calculation is based on
  the size and location of the associated Control, the size of the image used for the error icon as
  well as the value of the ImageAligment property.
Return value
  A TRect that defines the size and location where the control should be located. Note that this does
  not imply that the returned location is where the control is actually located. The returned values
  are in client coordinates and is directly assignment compatible with the <LINK TControl.BoundsRect,
  BoundsRect> property.
See Also
  TControl.BoundsRect

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvErrorControl.Control
Summary
  Specifies the control this error icon is acting on.
Description
  Read Control to determine what control this error icon is acting upon. Change Control to make the
  error icon act on another control. The size and location of the error icon is automatically adjusted
  depending on the location of Control, the value of ImageAlignment as well as the size of the image(s)
  in the image list Images.
See Also
  TJvErrorControl.ImageAlignment, TJvErrorControl.Images

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvErrorControl.DrawImage
Summary
  Method that draws the error icon.
Description
  DrawImage is called by the error indicator to draw or erase the error icon to simulate blinking the
  icon. Override this method in descendant classes to draw the icon differently. the error
Parameters
  Erase - set to false if the icon should be erased, false otherwise

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvErrorControl.Error
Summary
  Specifies the error message to display.
Description
  Use Error to set the message to display in the control. The error is displayed in a hint window when
  the user moves the mouse over the icon. Normally, Error is set by the error indicator that created
  the control.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvErrorControl.ImageAlignment
Summary
  Specifies where the error icon should be located.
Description
  Read ImageAlignment to determine where the error icon is located on the form. The value of
  ImageAlignment is relative to the Control it is associated with. Change ImageAlignment to move the
  error icon to another location.
See Also
  TJvErrorControl.Control

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvErrorControl.ImageIndex
Summary
  Specifies the image to display in the control.
Description
  ImageIndex is the index of the image in Images to display on the control. Set ImageIndex to -1 to not
  show any icon. Normally, this property is maintained by the error indicator that created the
  control.
See Also
  TJvErrorControl.Images

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvErrorControl.ImagePadding
Summary
  Specifies the padding around the images.
Description
  Use ImagePadding to make minor adjustments to the location of the image within the control. If
  ImagePadding is 0 or less, the image is centered within the control. The ImagePadding value is
  expressed in pixels.
See Also
  TJvErrorControl.ImageAlignment

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvErrorControl.Images
Summary
  Specifies the image list used to display images in the control.
Description
  Use Images to specify where the control retrieves its icons. In combination with ImageIndex
See Also
  TJvErrorControl.ImageIndex

