Summary
  \Controls where an error icon is displayed.
Description
  TJvErrorImageAlignment is the type used by the <LINK TJvErrorControl.ImageAlignment, ImageAlignment>
  property of error indicators and indicates where an error image should be placed in relation to the
  control it is associated with.

  Possible values for this type are:

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvErrorImageAlignment.eiaBottomLeft
  Displays the error image on the controls left side aligned to the bottom edge of the control.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvErrorImageAlignment.eiaBottomRight
  Displays the error image on the controls right side aligned to the bottom edge of the control.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvErrorImageAlignment.eiaMiddleLeft
  Displays the error image on the controls left side aligned to the middle of the control.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvErrorImageAlignment.eiaMiddleRight
  Displays the error image on the controls right side aligned to the middle of the control.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvErrorImageAlignment.eiaTopLeft
  Displays the error image on the controls left side aligned to the top edge of the control.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvErrorImageAlignment.eiaTopRight
  Displays the error image on the controls right side aligned to the top edge of the control.

