@@TJvErrorIndicator
<TITLEIMG TJvErrorIndicator>
JVCLInfo
  GROUP=JVCL.FormsAndApp.Forms.DecoratingAndEffects,JVCL.Graphics.Animations
  FLAG=Component
Summary
  Provides a user interface for indicating that a control on a form has an error associated with it.
Description
  Use an error indicator when you need to notify the user about an erroneous input value in a
  non-intrusive way. The error indicator uses the real estate of the form or dialog to display icons
  next to each control that has been determined to have an error. The icons Hint is also assigned the
  specific error message so when the user moves the mouse over the icon, the reason for the error is
  displayed.

  Although mainly used to display erroneous user input, this component can be used whenever you want to
  draw the users attention to a specific control or set of controls without having to show a dialog or
  similar.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvErrorIndicator.BeginUpdate
Summary
  Suspends screen repainting.
Description
  The BeginUpdate method suspends screen repainting until the EndUpdate method is called. Use
  BeginUpdate to speed processing and avoid flicker while errors are added to or deleted from the
  component.
See Also
  TJvErrorIndicator.EndUpdate

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvErrorIndicator.BlinkRate
Summary
  The rate at which the error image should flash.
Description
  Use BlinkRate to specify at what rate the error icons blink. The rate is expressed in milliseconds
  and the default is 250 milliseconds. A value of zero sets BlinkStyle to ebsNeverBlink. If BlinkStyle
  is ebsNeverBlink, this property have no effect.
See Also
  TJvErrorIndicator.BlinkStyle

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvErrorIndicator.BlinkStyle
Summary
  Specifies how blinking is performed.
Description
  Use BlinkStyle to specify how the error icons are blinked. For more information on the possible
  values of BlinkStyle, see the help topic on TJvErrorBlinkStyle.
See Also
  TJvErrorBlinkStyle

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvErrorIndicator.ClearErrors
Summary
  Removes all error icons.
Description
  Call ClearErrors to remove all error icons handled by this component with one call. After a call to
  ClearErrors, the internal error image list is emptied. Calling ClearErrors is the same as setting
  Error[nil] := '' but is slightly faster.
See Also
  Error

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvErrorIndicator.Controls
Summary
  Provides indexed access to the internal, protected list of TJvErrorControl instances.
Description
  Use \Controls to get direct access to the TJvErrorControl's that are maintained by the component.
See Also
  TJvErrorControl, TJvErrorIndicator.Count

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvErrorIndicator.Count
Summary
  Returns the number of controls in Controls.
Description
  Read Count to determine the number of TJvErrorControl objects in the Controls array.
See Also
  TJvErrorIndicator.Controls

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvErrorIndicator.EndUpdate
Summary
  Re-enables screen repainting
Description
  Use EndUpdate to re-enable screen repainting that was turned off with the BeginUpdate method.
See Also
  TJvErrorIndicator.BeginUpdate

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvErrorIndicator.Error
Summary
  Provides indexed access to each controls error messages.
Description
  Use Error along with the AControl parameter to access the error message associated with a control.
  Setting the error message to an empty string removes the error image (this is the only way to remove
  an error image for a single control). Use Error[nil] := 'SomeValue' to assign the error message
  'SomeValue' to all controls. Using Error[nil] := '' is equivalent to calling ClearErrors but
  ClearErrors is slightly faster.
See Also
  TJvErrorIndicator.Controls

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvErrorIndicator.ImageAlignment
Summary
  Specifies where the error icon should be located.
Description
  Use ImageAlignment along with AControl parameter to specify where the error icon should be located
  relative to AControl. If AControl is nil, ImageAlignment is set for all controls.
See Also
  TJvErrorIndicator.ImageIndex, Error

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvErrorIndicator.ImageIndex
Summary
  Specifies the image to display.
Description
  Use ImageIndex along with the AControl parameter to set the image to display for AControl. If
  AControl is nil, the ImageIndex is set for all controls.
See Also
  TJvErrorIndicator.ImageAlignment, Error

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvErrorIndicator.ImagePadding
Summary
  Specifies the padding around the images.
Description
  Use ImagePadding along with AControl to make minor adjustments to the location of the image within
  the control. If AControl is nil, ImagePadding affects all controls. If ImagePadding is 0 or less, the
  image is centered within the control.
See Also
  TJvErrorIndicator.ImageAlignment

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvErrorIndicator.Images
Summary
  Lists the images that can appear on the error icons.
Description
  Images contains a list of images that can appear on the error controls. Each error control’s
  ImageIndex property determines the specific image displayed on it. If Images is unassigned, no images
  are displayed on the error controls.

  Images in the list can be of any size, the error control will automatically adjust its size and
  position. To accommodate every system on which your application runs, it is recommended that you do
  not use 256 colors or higher.
See Also
  TJvErrorControl.ImageIndex, TJvErrorControl.Images, TJvErrorIndicator.ImageIndex

